130","Offaly, Ireland":"County Offaly, Irland","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England","England":"England","Athenry, County Galway, Ireland":"Athenry, County Galway, Irland","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England"},"nl":{"8 November 1104–4 June 1164":"8 november 1104–4 juni 1164","1104–1164":"1104–1164","1100–1175":"1100–1175","1124–1197":"1124–1197","1130–Male":"1130–Overleden","1141–Male":"1141–Overleden","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1078–1138":"1078–1138","1080":"1080","4 June 1164":"4 juni 1164","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1164":"1164","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","Abt 1124":"circa 1124","1124":"1124","8 November 1104":"8 november 1104","1078":"1078","1100":"1100","about 1130":"circa 1130","Offaly, Ireland":"County Offaly, Ierland","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Athenry, County Galway, Ireland":"Athenry, County Galway, Ierland","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England"},"en":{"8 November 1104–4 June 1164":"8 November 1104–4 June 1164","1104–1164":"1104–1164","1100–1175":"1100–1175","1124–1197":"1124–1197","1130–Male":"1130–Deceased","1141–Male":"1141–Deceased","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1078–1138":"1078–1138","1080":"1080","4 June 1164":"4 June 1164","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1164":"1164","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","Abt 1124":"about 1124","1124":"1124","8 November 1104":"8 November 1104","1078":"1078","1100":"1100","about 1130":"about 1130","Offaly, Ireland":"County Offaly, Ireland","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Athenry, County Galway, Ireland":"Athenry, County Galway, Ireland","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Birmingham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Birmingham in the West Midlands. In Domesday Book the name is already found as <i>Bermingeham</i>, but it seems likely that it was originally <i>Beornmundingahām</i> ‘homestead (Old English <i>hām</i>) of the people of (<i>-inga-</i>) <i>Beornmund</i>’, a personal name composed of the elements <i>beorn</i> ‘young man, warrior’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protection’. This surname is established in Ireland (see   Bermingham  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Burningham","meanings":["English (Surrey and Hampshire): variant of   Birmingham  ."]},{"name":"Bermingham","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Sinead.","Irish (of English origin): variant of   Birmingham  . This form of the surname is found mainly in Ireland.","History: The Bermingham family take their surname from lands held at what is now a great city in the West Midlands of England, but it was brought to Ireland as early as the 12th century. The Norman baron Robert de Bermyngeham was a follower of Strongbow (see   Clare  ); his name is found on a number of Irish charters between 1175 and 1179. The family was also known as <i>Mac Fheorais</i> (see   Corish  ) in Ireland, named for Piers (Gaelic <i>Feoras</i>) de Bermyngeham, the father of Robert."]}]},{"name":"Piers","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Regular medieval vernacular form of   Peter   (from the Old French nominative case, as against the oblique <i>Pier</i>, modern <i>Pierre</i>). In the form <i>Pierce</i> it survived into the 18th century, although in part this may be a transferred use of the surname derived from the medieval given name. <i>Piers</i> was revived in the mid-20th century, perhaps partly under the influence of  William Langland's  great rambling medieval poem Piers Plowman (  1367–86 ), in which the character of Piers symbolizes the virtues of hard work, honesty, and fairness."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":1,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Piers Birmingham was born on 8 November 1104, in Birmingham, Warwickshire, England, his father, William de Bermingham, was 24 and his mother, Isobel de Bernigham, was 26. He had at least 3 sons with Catherine de Kingsley. He died on 4 June 1164, in Athenry, County Galway, Ireland, at the age of 59."},"et":{"8 November 1104–4 June 1164":"8. november 1104–4. juuni 1164","1104–1164":"1104–1164","1100–1175":"1100–1175","1124–1197":"1124–1197","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1078–1138":"1078–1138","1080":"1080","4 June 1164":"4. juuni 1164","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1164":"1164","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","Abt 1124":"umbes 1124","1124":"1124","8 November 1104":"8. november 1104","1078":"1078","1100":"1100","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Offaly, Ireland":"County Offaly, Iirimaa","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Athenry, County Galway, Ireland":"Athenry, County Galway, Iirimaa","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"8 November 1104–4 June 1164":"8. marraskuuta 1104–4. kesäkuuta 1164","1104–1164":"1104–1164","1100–1175":"1100–1175","1124–1197":"1124–1197","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1141–Male":"1141–Kuollut","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1078–1138":"1078–1138","1080":"1080","4 June 1164":"4. kesäkuuta 1164","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1164":"1164","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","Abt 1124":"noin 1124","1124":"1124","8 November 1104":"8. marraskuuta 1104","1078":"1078","1100":"1100","about 1130":"noin 1130","Offaly, Ireland":"County Offaly, Irlanti","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":